        <!-- Quiz Content -->
        <div class="quiz-content">
            <!-- Question 1: Vocabulary -->
            <div class="question-card active" data-question="1">
                <div class="question-number">1</div>
                <div class="question-text">What does "boarding gate" mean in French?</div>
                <div class="options-container">
                    <div class="option" data-answer="a">
                        <span class="option-letter">A</span>
                        <span class="option-text">Porte d'entrée</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="b">
                        <span class="option-letter">B</span>
                        <span class="option-text">Porte d'embarquement</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="c">
                        <span class="option-letter">C</span>
                        <span class="option-text">Porte de sortie</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="d">
                        <span class="option-letter">D</span>
                        <span class="option-text">Porte de sécurité</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="explanation">
                    <h4>✅ Correct Answer: B</h4>
                    <p><strong>"Boarding gate"</strong> = <em>"Porte d'embarquement"</em><br>
                    This is where passengers wait to board their aircraft. Essential vocabulary for airport customer service.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 2: Courtesy Phrases -->
            <div class="question-card" data-question="2">
                <div class="question-number">2</div>
                <div class="question-text">How do you politely ask for a passenger's boarding pass?</div>
                <div class="options-container">
                    <div class="option" data-answer="a">
                        <span class="option-letter">A</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"Give me your boarding pass"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Donnez-moi votre carte d'embarquement</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="b">
                        <span class="option-letter">B</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"Could you please show me your boarding pass?"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Pourriez-vous me montrer votre carte d'embarquement ?</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="c">
                        <span class="option-letter">C</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"Where is your boarding pass?"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Où est votre carte d'embarquement ?</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="d">
                        <span class="option-letter">D</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"I need to see your boarding pass"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">J'ai besoin de voir votre carte d'embarquement</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="explanation">
                    <h4>✅ Correct Answer: B</h4>
                    <p><strong>"Could you please show me your boarding pass?"</strong> is the most polite and professional way to make this request. Using "could you please" shows courtesy and respect.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 3: Directions -->
            <div class="question-card" data-question="3">
                <div class="question-number">3</div>
                <div class="question-text">A passenger asks: "Where is gate C15?" What's the best response?</div>
                <div class="options-container">
                    <div class="option" data-answer="a">
                        <span class="option-letter">A</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"I don't know"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Je ne sais pas</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="b">
                        <span class="option-letter">B</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"It's over there"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">C'est par là</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="c">
                        <span class="option-letter">C</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"Go straight ahead, then turn left after the duty-free shop"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Allez tout droit, puis tournez à gauche après le duty-free</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="d">
                        <span class="option-letter">D</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"Find it yourself"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Trouvez-le vous-même</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="explanation">
                    <h4>✅ Correct Answer: C</h4>
                    <p>Clear, specific directions help passengers navigate efficiently. Always provide landmarks and clear instructions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 4: Phone Communication -->
            <div class="question-card" data-question="4">
                <div class="question-number">4</div>
                <div class="question-text">How should you answer the phone at an airport information desk?</div>
                <div class="options-container">
                    <div class="option" data-answer="a">
                        <span class="option-letter">A</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"Hello"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Bonjour</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="b">
                        <span class="option-letter">B</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"Good morning, Airport information desk, how can I assist you?"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Bonjour, bureau d'information de l'aéroport, comment puis-je vous aider ?</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="c">
                        <span class="option-letter">C</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"Yes?"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Oui ?</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="d">
                        <span class="option-letter">D</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"What do you want?"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Que voulez-vous ?</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="explanation">
                    <h4>✅ Correct Answer: B</h4>
                    <p>Professional phone greetings should include: location identification, your role, and an offer to help.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 5: Problem Management -->
            <div class="question-card" data-question="5">
                <div class="question-number">5</div>
                <div class="question-text">A passenger says: "My flight is delayed!" How do you respond professionally?</div>
                <div class="options-container">
                    <div class="option" data-answer="a">
                        <span class="option-letter">A</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"That's not my problem"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Ce n'est pas mon problème</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="b">
                        <span class="option-letter">B</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"I'm sorry for the inconvenience. Let me check the latest updates for you"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Je suis désolé pour le dérangement. Laissez-moi vérifier les dernières mises à jour</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="c">
                        <span class="option-letter">C</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"Delays happen all the time"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Les retards arrivent tout le temps</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="d">
                        <span class="option-letter">D</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"You should have checked before coming"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Vous auriez dû vérifier avant de venir</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="explanation">
                    <h4>✅ Correct Answer: B</h4>
                    <p>Always acknowledge the customer's concern, apologize for the inconvenience, and offer to help with specific actions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 6: Listening Comprehension -->
            <div class="question-card" data-question="6">
                <div class="question-number">6</div>
                <div class="question-text">Listen to this airport announcement:</div>
                <div class="question-audio">
                    🎧 Audio: "Flight BA2051 to Madrid is now boarding at gate A7. This is the final call for passengers."
                </div>
                <div class="question-text">What should passengers do?</div>
                <div class="options-container">
                    <div class="option" data-answer="a">
                        <span class="option-letter">A</span>
                        <span class="option-text">Wait in the lounge</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Attendre dans le salon</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="b">
                        <span class="option-letter">B</span>
                        <span class="option-text">Go immediately to gate A7</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Aller immédiatement à la porte A7</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="c">
                        <span class="option-letter">C</span>
                        <span class="option-text">Check in their luggage</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Enregistrer leurs bagages</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="d">
                        <span class="option-letter">D</span>
                        <span class="option-text">Go through security</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Passer la sécurité</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="explanation">
                    <h4>✅ Correct Answer: B</h4>
                    <p><strong>"Final call"</strong> means this is the last announcement before the gate closes. Passengers must go immediately to gate A7.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 7: Vocabulary - Services -->
            <div class="question-card" data-question="7">
                <div class="question-number">7</div>
                <div class="question-text">What does "baggage claim" mean?</div>
                <div class="options-container">
                    <div class="option" data-answer="a">
                        <span class="option-letter">A</span>
                        <span class="option-text">Enregistrement des bagages</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="b">
                        <span class="option-letter">B</span>
                        <span class="option-text">Contrôle des bagages</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="c">
                        <span class="option-letter">C</span>
                        <span class="option-text">Retrait des bagages</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="d">
                        <span class="option-letter">D</span>
                        <span class="option-text">Perte des bagages</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="explanation">
                    <h4>✅ Correct Answer: C</h4>
                    <p><strong>"Baggage claim"</strong> is where passengers collect their checked luggage after arriving at their destination.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 8: Customer Service Scenario -->
            <div class="question-card" data-question="8">
                <div class="question-number">8</div>
                <div class="question-text">A passenger says: "I can't find my suitcase at baggage claim!" What's your best response?</div>
                <div class="options-container">
                    <div class="option" data-answer="a">
                        <span class="option-letter">A</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"It's lost forever"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Il est perdu à jamais</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="b">
                        <span class="option-letter">B</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"Please come with me to the lost luggage office. We'll fill out a form together"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Veuillez me suivre au bureau des objets perdus. Nous remplirons un formulaire ensemble</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="c">
                        <span class="option-letter">C</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"That's the airline's problem"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">C'est le problème de la compagnie aérienne</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="d">
                        <span class="option-letter">D</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"Look harder"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Cherchez mieux</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="explanation">
                    <h4>✅ Correct Answer: B</h4>
                    <p>Take immediate action to help solve the problem. Guide the passenger to the appropriate office and assist with the process.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 9: Formal/Informal Language -->
            <div class="question-card" data-question="9">
                <div class="question-number">9</div>
                <div class="question-text">Which phrase is most appropriate for professional airport customer service?</div>
                <div class="options-container">
                    <div class="option" data-answer="a">
                        <span class="option-letter">A</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"Yeah, sure, whatever"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Ouais, bien sûr, peu importe</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="b">
                        <span class="option-letter">B</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"I'd be happy to assist you with that"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Je serai ravi de vous aider avec cela</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="c">
                        <span class="option-letter">C</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"I dunno"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">J'sais pas</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="d">
                        <span class="option-letter">D</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"Not my job"</span>
                        <div class="option-translation">Pas mon travail</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="explanation">
                    <h4>✅ Correct Answer: B</h4>
                    <p>Professional language should be polite, positive, and helpful. Avoid informal expressions and negative responses.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 10: Time and Numbers -->
            <div class="question-card" data-question="10">
                <div class="question-number">10</div>
                <div class="question-text">How do you say "The flight departs at 14:30" in conversational English?</div>
                <div class="options-container">
                    <div class="option" data-answer="a">
                        <span class="option-letter">A</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"The flight departs at fourteen thirty"</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="b">
                        <span class="option-letter">B</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"The flight departs at two thirty PM"</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="c">
                        <span class="option-letter">C</span>
                        <span class="option-text">"The flight departs at half past two in the afternoon"</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="option" data-answer="d">
                        <span class="option-letter">D</span>
                        <span class="option-text">All of the above are correct</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="explanation">
                    <h4>✅ Correct Answer: D</h4>
                    <p>All three ways are correct for expressing 14:30. In airport customer service, you can use military time, 12-hour format, or conversational time expressions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

